"Read the supported hardware list that shipped with the version of FreeBSD to be installed and verify that the system's hardware is supported."
msgstr "阅读将要安装的 FreeBSD 版本所支持的硬件列表，并确认系统的硬件被支持。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "Minimum Hardware Requirements"
msgstr "最低硬件要求"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:92
msgid ""
"The hardware requirements to install FreeBSD vary by architecture.  Hardware architectures and devices supported by a FreeBSD release are listed "
"on the link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/releases/[FreeBSD Release Information] page.  The link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/where/[FreeBSD download page] "
"also has recommendations for choosing the correct image for different architectures."
msgstr ""
"安装 FreeBSD 的硬件要求因架构而异。FreeBSD 发行版本所支持的硬件架构和设备会在 link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/releases/[FreeBSD 发行信息]页面上列出。"
"在 FreeBSD 的 link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/where/[下载页面] 上也有针对不同架构选择正确镜像的建议。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:97
msgid ""
"A FreeBSD installation requires a minimum of 96 MB of RAM and 1.5 GB of free hard drive space.  However, such small amounts of memory and disk "
"space are really only suitable for custom applications like embedded appliances.  General-purpose desktop systems need more resources.  2-4 GB "
"RAM and at least 8 GB hard drive space is a good starting point."
msgstr ""
"安装 FreeBSD 至少需要 96 MB 的内存和 1.5 GB 的可用硬盘空间。然而，这样小的内存和磁盘空间确实只适合于像嵌入式设备这样的定制应用。通用的桌面系统需要"
"更多的资源。2-4GB 内存和至少 8GB 硬盘空间是一个好的选择。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:99
msgid "These are the processor requirements for each architecture:"
msgstr "这些是每个架构的处理器要求："

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:100
#, no-wrap
msgid "amd64"
msgstr "amd64"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:104
msgid ""
"This is the most common desktop and laptop processor type, used in most modern systems.  Intel(R) calls it Intel64.  Other manufacturers "
"sometimes call it x86-64."
msgstr "这是最常见的台式机和笔记本电脑处理器类型，并在大多数现代系统中使用。Intel(R) 称其为 Intel64。其他制造商有时称它为 x86-64。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:106
msgid ""
"Examples of amd64 compatible processors include: AMD Athlon(TM)64, AMD Opteron(TM), multi-core Intel(R) Xeon(TM), and Intel(R) Core(TM) 2 and "
"later processors."
msgstr "兼容 amd64 的处理器的例子包括：AMD Athlon(TM) 64、AMD Opteron(TM)、多核 Intel(R) Xeon(TM) 和 Intel(R) Core(TM) 2 及以后的处理器。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "i386"
msgstr "i386"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:109
msgid "Older desktops and laptops often use this 32-bit, x86 architecture."
msgstr "老式台式机和笔记本电脑通常使用这种 32 位的 X86 架构。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:113
msgid ""
"Almost all i386-compatible processors with a floating point unit are supported.  All Intel(R) processors 486 or higher are supported.  However, "
"binaries released by the project are compiled for the 686 processor, so a special build will be needed for 486 and 586 systems."
msgstr ""
"几乎所有与 i386 兼容的带有浮点单元的处理器都被支持。所有 486 或更高的 Intel(R) 处理器都被支持。然而，由该项目发布的二进制文件是为 686 处理器编译"
"的，所以 486 和 586 系统需要进行特殊的编译。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:117
msgid ""
"FreeBSD will take advantage of Physical Address Extensions (PAE) support on CPUs with this feature.  A kernel with the PAE feature enabled will "
"detect memory above 4 GB and allow it to be used by the system.  However, using PAE places constraints on device drivers and other features of "
"FreeBSD."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 将利用物理地址扩展（PAE）对具有这一特性的 CPU 的支持。启用了 PAE 功能的内核会检测到超过 4GB 的内存，并允许系统使用它。然而，使用 PAE 会对"
"设备驱动和 FreeBSD 的其他功能造成限制。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "arm64"
msgstr "arm64"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:121
msgid "Most embedded boards are 64-bit ARM computers.  A number of arm64 servers are supported."
msgstr "大多数嵌入式板卡是 64 位的 ARM 计算机。一些 arm64 服务器可被支持。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:122
#, no-wrap
msgid "arm"
msgstr "arm"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:124
msgid "Older armv7 boards are supported."
msgstr "支持较早的 armv7 板卡。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "powerpc"
msgstr "powerpc"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:128
msgid "All New World ROM Apple(R) Mac(R) systems with built-in USB are supported.  SMP is supported on machines with multiple CPUs."
msgstr "支持所有具有内置 USB 的 New World ROM Apple(R) Mac(R) 系统。在有多个 CPU 的机器上支持 SMP。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:130
msgid "A 32-bit kernel can only use the first 2 GB of RAM."
msgstr "32 位的内核只能使用前 2GB 的 RAM。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:132
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pre-Installation Tasks"
msgstr "安装前的准备工作"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:136
msgid ""
"Once it has been determined that the system meets the minimum hardware requirements for installing FreeBSD, the installation file should be "
"downloaded and the installation media prepared.  Before doing this, check that the system is ready for an installation by verifying the items in "
"this checklist:"
msgstr ""
"在确定系统符合安装 FreeBSD 的最低硬件要求之后，就应该下载安装文件并准备好安装介质。在这之前，请检查系统是否已经准备好进行安装，方法是检查这个表中"
"的项目："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Back Up Important Data*\n"
msgstr "*备份重要数据*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:145
msgid ""
"Before installing any operating system, _always_ backup all important data first.  Do not store the backup on the system being installed.  "
"Instead, save the data to a removable disk such as a USB drive, another system on the network, or an online backup service.  Test the backup "
"before starting the installation to make sure it contains all of the needed files.  Once the installer formats the system's disk, all data stored "
"on that disk will be lost."
msgstr ""
"在安装任何操作系统之前，_总是_先备份所有的重要数据。不要将备份存储在正在安装的系统上。相反，应将数据保存在可移动磁盘上，如 USB 驱动器，网络上的另"
"一个系统，或在线备份服务。在开始安装前测试备份，以确保它包含所有需要的文件。只要安装程序格式化了系统的磁盘，存储在该磁盘上的所有数据就会丢失。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Decide Where to Install FreeBSD*\n"
msgstr "*决定在哪里安装 FreeBSD*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:149
msgid ""
"If FreeBSD will be the only operating system installed, this step can be skipped.  But if FreeBSD will share the disk with another operating "
"system, decide which disk or partition will be used for FreeBSD."
msgstr "如果 FreeBSD 是唯一安装的操作系统，这一步就可以跳过。但如果 FreeBSD 将与其他操作系统共享磁盘，请决定哪个磁盘或分区将被用于安装 FreeBSD。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:156
msgid ""
"In the i386 and amd64 architectures, disks can be divided into multiple partitions using one of two partitioning schemes.  A traditional _Master "
"Boot Record_ (MBR) holds a partition table defining up to four _primary partitions_.  For historical reasons, FreeBSD calls these primary "
"partition _slices_.  One of these primary partitions can be made into an _extended partition_ containing multiple _logical partitions_.  The "
"_GUID Partition Table_ (GPT) is a newer and simpler method of partitioning a disk.  Common GPT implementations allow up to 128 partitions per "
"disk, eliminating the need for logical partitions."
msgstr ""
"在 i386 和 amd64 架构中，磁盘可以通过两种分区方案之一被划分为多个分区。传统的_主引导记录_（MBR）拥有一个定义了最多四个_主分区_的分区表。由于历史原"
"因，FreeBSD 将这些主分区称为_片区_。这些主分区中的一个可以被制作成包含多个_逻辑分区_的_扩展分区_。_GUID 分区表_（GPT）是一种较新的、较简单的磁盘分"
"区方法。常见的 GPT 实现允许每个磁盘有多达 128 个分区，消除了对逻辑分区的需求。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:160
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD boot loader requires either a primary or GPT partition.  If all of the primary or GPT partitions are already in use, one must be "
"freed for FreeBSD.  To create a partition without deleting existing data, use a partition resizing tool to shrink an existing partition and "
"create a new partition using the freed space."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 启动加载器需要一个主分区或 GPT 分区。如果所有的主分区或 GPT 分区都已经被使用，则必须为 FreeBSD 腾出一个分区。要在不删除现有数据的情况下创"
"建一个分区，可以使用分区调整工具来缩小现有的分区，并利用释放的空间创建一个新的分区。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:164
msgid ""
"A variety of free and commercial partition resizing tools are listed at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_disk_partitioning_software[http://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_disk_partitioning_software].  GParted Live (https://gparted.org/livecd.php[https://gparted.org/livecd.php]) is a free "
"live CD which includes the GParted partition editor.  GParted is also included with many other Linux live CD distributions."
msgstr ""
"各种免费的和商业的分区调整工具列在 http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_disk_partitioning_software[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"List_of_disk_partitioning_software] 。GParted Live (https://gparted.org/livecd.php[https://gparted.org/livecd.php]) 是一张免费的 Live CD，其中包"
"括 GParted 分区编辑器。GParted 也包括在许多其他的 Linux Live CD 发行中。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:169
msgid ""
"When used properly, disk shrinking utilities can safely create space for creating a new partition.  Since the possibility of selecting the wrong "
"partition exists, always backup any important data and verify the integrity of the backup before modifying disk partitions."
msgstr ""
"如果使用得当，磁盘缩减工具可以安全地创造空间来创建一个新的分区。由于存在选择错误分区的可能性，因此在修改磁盘分区之前，一定要备份任何重要数据，并验"
"证备份的完整性。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:173
msgid ""
"Disk partitions containing different operating systems make it possible to install multiple operating systems on one computer.  An alternative is "
"to use virtualization (crossref:virtualization[virtualization,Virtualization]) which allows multiple operating systems to run at the same time "
"without modifying any disk partitions."
msgstr ""
"包含不同操作系统的磁盘分区使得在一台计算机上安装多个操作系统成为可能。另一种方法是使用(crossref:virtualization[virtualization,虚拟化])"
"（Virtualization），它允许多个操作系统同时运行，而无需修改任何磁盘分区。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:174
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Collect Network Information*\n"
msgstr "*收集网络信息*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:177
msgid ""
"Some FreeBSD installation methods require a network connection in order to download the installation files.  After any installation, the "
"installer will offer to setup the system's network interfaces."
msgstr "一些 FreeBSD 安装方法需要网络连接以下载安装文件。在任何安装之后，安装程序都会提出要设置系统的网络接口。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:180
msgid ""
"If the network has a DHCP server, it can be used to provide automatic network configuration.  If DHCP is not available, the following network "
"information for the system must be obtained from the local network administrator or Internet service provider:"
msgstr ""
"如果网络有 DHCP 服务器，可以用它来提供自动的网络配置。如果 DHCP 不可用，则必须从本地网络管理员或互联网服务提供商那里获得系统的下列网络信息："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:183
msgid "Required Network Information"
msgstr "所需的网络信息"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:185
msgid "IP address"
msgstr "IP 地址"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:186
msgid "Subnet mask"
msgstr "子网掩码"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:187
msgid "IP address of default gateway"
msgstr "默认网关的 IP 地址"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:188
msgid "Domain name of the network"
msgstr "网络的域名"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:189
msgid "IP addresses of the network's DNS servers"
msgstr "网络的 DNS 服务器的 IP 地址"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Check for FreeBSD Errata*\n"
msgstr "*检查 FreeBSD 的勘误表*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:196
msgid ""
"Although the FreeBSD Project strives to ensure that each release of FreeBSD is as stable as possible, bugs occasionally creep into the process.  "
"On very rare occasions those bugs affect the installation process.  As these problems are discovered and fixed, they are noted in the FreeBSD "
"Errata (link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/releases/{rel130-current}R/errata/[https://www.freebsd.org/releases/{rel130-current}R/errata/]) on the "
"FreeBSD web site.  Check the errata before installing to make sure that there are no problems that might affect the installation."
msgstr ""
"尽管 FreeBSD 项目努力确保每个版本的 FreeBSD 都是尽可能的稳定，但偶尔也会有一些 bug 悄悄发生这个过程。在非常罕见的情况下，这些错误会影响安装过程。"
"当这些问题被发现和修正时，它们会在 FreeBSD 网站上的 FreeBSD 勘误表 (link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/releases/{rel130-current}R/errata/[https://www."
"freebsd.org/releases/{rel130-current}R/errata/]) 中注明。在安装前请检查勘误表，以确保没有可能影响安装的问题。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:198
msgid ""
"Information and errata for all the releases can be found on the release information section of the FreeBSD web site (link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/"
"releases/[https://www.freebsd.org/releases/])."
msgstr ""
"所有发行版的信息和勘误表可以在 FreeBSD 网站上的发行信息部分找到 (link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/releases/[https://www.freebsd.org/releases/])。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:200
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prepare the Installation Media"
msgstr "准备好安装介质"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:204
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD installer is not an application that can be run from within another operating system.  Instead, download a FreeBSD installation file, "
"burn it to the media associated with its file type and size (CD, DVD, or USB), and boot the system to install from the inserted media."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 安装程序不是一个可以从其他操作系统中运行的应用程序。取而代之的是，下载一个 FreeBSD 安装文件，将其刻录到与其文件类型和大小相关的介质上"
"（CD、DVD 或 USB），然后从插入的介质启动系统进行安装。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:208
msgid ""
"FreeBSD installation files are available at link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/where/[www.freebsd.org/where/].  Each installation file's name includes "
"the release version of FreeBSD, the architecture, and the type of file.  For example, to install FreeBSD 13.0 on an amd64 system from a DVD, "
"download [.filename]#FreeBSD-13.0-RELEASE-amd64-dvd1.iso#, burn this file to a DVD, and boot the system with the DVD inserted."
msgstr ""
"可以在 link:https://www.FreeBSD.org/where/[www.freebsd.org/where/] 找到 FreeBSD 的安装文件。每个安装文件的名称都包括 FreeBSD 的发行版本、架构和文"
"件类型。例如，如果要在 amd64 系统上安装 FreeBSD 13.0，请下载 [.filename]#FreeBSD-13.0-RELEASE-amd64-dvd1.iso#，把这个文件刻录到 DVD 上，然后在插"
"入 DVD 的情况下启动系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:211
msgid "Installation files are available in several formats.  The formats vary depending on computer architecture and media type."
msgstr "安装文件有几种格式。这些格式因计算机结构和介质类型而异。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:215
msgid ""
"Additional installation files are included for computers that boot with UEFI (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface).  The names of these files "
"include the string [.filename]#uefi#."
msgstr "对于使用 UEFI（统一可扩展固件接口）启动的计算机，还包括其他安装文件。这些文件的名称包括 [.filename]#uefi# 这个字符串。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:217
msgid "File types:"
msgstr "文件类型："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:219
msgid ""
"`-bootonly.iso`: This is the smallest installation file as it only contains the installer. A working Internet connection is required during "
"installation as the installer will download the files it needs to complete the FreeBSD installation. This file should be burned to a CD using a "
"CD burning application."
msgstr ""
"`-bootonly.iso`：这是最小的安装文件，因为它只包含安装程序。在安装过程中需要一个正常的互联网连接，因为安装程序会下载 FreeBSD 安装所需的文件。应该用"
"光盘刻录软件把这个文件刻录到光盘上。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:220
msgid ""
"`-disc1.iso`: This file contains all of the files needed to install FreeBSD, its source, and the Ports Collection. It should be burned to a CD "
"using a CD burning application."
msgstr "`-disc1.iso`：这个文件包含了安装 FreeBSD 所需的所有文件，包含 FreeBSD 的源代码，以及 Ports Collection。应使用光盘刻录软件将其刻录到光盘上。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:221
msgid ""
"`-dvd1.iso`: This file contains all of the files needed to install FreeBSD, its source, and the Ports Collection. It also contains a set of "
"popular binary packages for installing a window manager and some applications so that a complete system can be installed from media without "
"requiring a connection to the Internet. This file should be burned to a DVD using a DVD burning application."
msgstr ""
"`-dvd1.iso`：这个文件包含了安装 FreeBSD、其源代码和 Ports Collection 所需的所有文件。它还包含了一套用于安装窗口管理器和一些应用程序的常用二进制"
"包，这样就可以从安装介质中安装一个完整的系统，而不需要连接到互联网。应该用 DVD 刻录程序把这个文件刻录到 DVD 上。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:222
msgid ""
"`-memstick.img`: This file contains all of the files needed to install FreeBSD, its source, and the Ports Collection. It should be burned to a "
"USB stick using the instructions below."
msgstr "`-memstick.img`：这个文件包含了安装 FreeBSD 所需的所有文件，以及其源代码和 Ports Collection。应该按照下面的说明把它刻录到 U 盘上。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:223
msgid ""
"`-mini-memstick.img`: Like `-bootonly.iso`, does not include installation files, but downloads them as needed. A working internet connection is "
"required during installation. Write this file to a USB stick as shown in <<bsdinstall-usb>>."
msgstr ""
"`-mini-memstick.img`：和 `-bootonly.iso` 一样，不包括安装文件，但会根据需要下载它们。在安装过程中需要一个正常的互联网连接。如<<bsdinstall-usb>>所"
"示，将此文件写入U盘。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:228
msgid ""
"After downloading the image file, download [.filename]#CHECKSUM.SHA256# from the same directory.  Calculate a _checksum_ for the image file.  "
"FreeBSD provides man:sha256[1] for this, used as `sha256 _imagefilename_`.  Other operating systems have similar programs."
msgstr ""
"下载镜像文件后，从同一目录中下载 [.filename]#CHECKSUM.SHA256#。计算映像文件的_校验和_。FreeBSD 为此提供了 man:sha256[1] ，通过命令 `sha256 "
"_imagefilename_` 来使用。其他操作系统也有类似的程序。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:232
msgid ""
"Compare the calculated checksum with the one shown in [.filename]#CHECKSUM.SHA256#.  The checksums must match exactly.  If the checksums do not "
"match, the image file is corrupt and must be downloaded again."
msgstr ""
"将计算出来的校验和与 [.filename]#CHECKSUM.SHA256# 中显示的校验和进行比较。这些校验和必须完全匹配。如果校验和不匹配，就镜像文件损坏了，必须重新下"
"载。"

#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "Writing an Image File to USB"
msgstr "将镜像写入 USB 设备"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:240
msgid ""
"The [.filename]#\\*.img# file is an _image_ of the complete contents of a memory stick.  It _cannot_ be copied to the target device as a file.  "
"Several applications are available for writing the [.filename]#*.img# to a USB stick.  This section describes two of these utilities."
msgstr ""
"[.filename]#\\*.img# 文件是一个 U 盘完整的_映像_。它_不能_作为文件被复制到目标设备上。有几个应用程序可用于将 [.filename]#\\*.img# 写入 U 盘。本节"
"将介绍其中的两个软件。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:245
msgid "Before proceeding, back up any important data on the USB stick.  This procedure will erase the existing data on the stick."
msgstr "在继续进行之前，请备份 U 盘上一切重要的数据。这个程序将删除 U 盘上的现有数据。"

#. type: delimited block * 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Procedure. Using `dd` to Write the Image* +\n"
msgstr "*方法。使用 `dd` 刻录镜像* +\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:256
msgid ""
"This example uses [.filename]#/dev/da0# as the target device where the image will be written.  Be _very careful_ that the correct device is used "
"as this command will destroy the existing data on the specified target device."
msgstr ""
"这个例子使用 [.filename]#/dev/da0# 作为目标设备，镜像将被写入该设备。要_非常小心_使用正确的设备，因为这个命令会破坏指定的目标设备上的现有数据。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:259
msgid ""
"The command-line utility is available on BSD, Linux(R), and Mac OS(R) systems. To burn the image using `dd`, insert the USB stick and determine "
"its device name. Then, specify the name of the downloaded installation file and the device name for the USB stick. This example burns the amd64 "
"installation image to the first USB device on an existing FreeBSD system."
msgstr ""
"这个命令行工具在 BSD、Linux(R) 和 Mac OS(R) 系统上可用。要使用 `dd` 刻录镜像，插入 U 盘并确定其设备名称。然后，指定下载的安装文件的名称和 U 盘的设"
"备名称。这个例子将 amd64 安装镜像刻录到现有 FreeBSD 系统的第一个 USB 设备上。"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:263
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dd if=FreeBSD-13.0-RELEASE-amd64-memstick.img of=/dev/da0 bs=1M conv=sync\n"
msgstr "# dd if=FreeBSD-13.0-RELEASE-amd64-memstick.img of=/dev/da0 bs=1M conv=sync\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:270
msgid ""
"If this command fails, verify that the USB stick is not mounted and that the device name is for the disk, not a partition.  Some operating "
"systems might require this command to be run with man:sudo[8].  The man:dd[1] syntax varies slightly across different platforms; for example, Mac "
"OS(R) requires a lower-case `bs=1m`.  Systems like Linux(R) might buffer writes.  To force all writes to complete, use man:sync[8]."
msgstr ""
"如果这个命令执行失败，请确认 U 盘有无被挂载，且设备名称应是磁盘的名称，而不是一个分区。一些操作系统可能要求这个命令必须在 man:sudo[8] 下运行。man:"
"dd[1]的语法在不同的平台上略有不同；例如，Mac OS(R) 需要小写的 bs=1m。像 Linux(R) 这样的系统可能会对写入进行缓冲。要强制所有的写操作完成，请使用 "
"man:sync[8]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:275
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Procedure. Using Windows(R) to Write the Image* +\n"
msgstr "*方法。使用 Windows(R) 刻录镜像* +\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:280
msgid "Be sure to give the correct drive letter as the existing data on the specified drive will be overwritten and destroyed."
msgstr "请确保给出正确的盘符，因为指定驱动器上的现有数据将被覆盖和销毁。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:282
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Obtaining Image Writer for Windows(R)*\n"
msgstr "*获得用于 Windows(R) 的 Image Writer*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:285
msgid ""
"Image Writer for Windows(R) is a free application that can correctly write an image file to a memory stick.  Download it from https://sourceforge."
"net/projects/win32diskimager/[https://sourceforge.net/projects/win32diskimager/] and extract it into a folder."
msgstr ""
"Image Writer for Windows(R) 是一个免费的应用程序，可以正确地将镜像文件写入存储器。从 https://sourceforge.net/projects/win32diskimager/[https://"
"sourceforge.net/projects/win32diskimager/] 下载，并将其解压到一个文件夹中。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:287
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Writing the Image with Image Writer*\n"
msgstr "*用 Image Writer 写入镜像*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:294
msgid ""
"Double-click the Win32DiskImager icon to start the program.  Verify that the drive letter shown under `Device` is the drive with the memory "
"stick.  Click the folder icon and select the image to be written to the memory stick.  Click btn:[Save] to accept the image file name.  Verify "
"that everything is correct, and that no folders on the memory stick are open in other windows.  When everything is ready, click btn:[Write] to "
"write the image file to the memory stick."
msgstr ""
"双击 Win32DiskImager 图标以启动该程序。确认 `Device` 下显示的盘符是装有 USB 设备的驱动器。点击文件夹图标，选择要写入 U 盘的镜像。点击 btn:[Save]，"
"接受镜像文件名。确认一切都正确，并且 U 盘的文件夹没有在其他窗口中打开。一切准备就绪后，点击 btn:[Write]，将镜像文件写入存储器。"

#. type: delimited block * 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:297
msgid "You are now ready to start installing FreeBSD."
msgstr "现在你已经准备好，可以开始安装 FreeBSD 了。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "Starting the Installation"
msgstr "开始安装"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:304
msgid "By default, the installation will not make any changes to the disk(s) before the following message:"
msgstr "默认情况下，在出现以下信息之前，安装不会对磁盘进行任何修改："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:311
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Your changes will now be written to disk. If you\n"
"have chosen to overwrite existing data, it will\n"
"be PERMANENTLY ERASED. Are you sure you want to\n"
"commit your changes?\n"
msgstr ""
"Your changes will now be written to disk. If you\n"
"have chosen to overwrite existing data, it will\n"
"be PERMANENTLY ERASED. Are you sure you want to\n"
"commit your changes?\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:315
msgid ""
"The install can be exited at any time prior to this warning.  If there is a concern that something is incorrectly configured, just turn the "
"computer off before this point and no changes will be made to the system's disks."
msgstr "在此之前均可安全退出。如果担心有什么地方配置不正确，只要在这之前关闭计算机，系统的磁盘就不会有任何变化。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:321
msgid ""
"This section describes how to boot the system from the installation media which was prepared using the instructions in <<bsdinstall-installation-"
"media>>.  When using a bootable USB stick, plug in the USB stick before turning on the computer.  When booting from CD or DVD, turn on the "
"computer and insert the media at the first opportunity.  How to configure the system to boot from the inserted media depends upon the "
"architecture."
msgstr ""
"本节介绍了如何从安装介质启动系统，安装介质是按照 <<bsdinstall-installation-media>> 中的说明准备的。当使用可启动的 U 盘时，在打开计算机之前插入 U "
"盘。当从 CD 或 DVD 启动时，请在第一时间打开计算机并插入媒体。如何配置系统以从插入的媒体启动，取决于架构。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting on i386(TM) and amd64"
msgstr "在 i386(TM) 和 amd64 上启动"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:329
msgid ""
"These architectures provide a BIOS menu for selecting the boot device.  Depending upon the installation media being used, select the CD/DVD or "
"USB device as the first boot device.  Most systems also provide a key for selecting the boot device during startup without having to enter the "
"BIOS.  Typically, the key is either kbd:[F10], kbd:[F11], kbd:[F12], or kbd:[Escape]."
msgstr ""
"这些架构提供了一个 BIOS 菜单来选择启动设备。根据所使用的安装介质，选择 CD/DVD 或 USB 设备作为第一启动设备。大多数系统还提供了一个键，用于在启动过"
"程中选择启动设备，而不需要进入 BIOS。一般来说，这个键是 kbd:[F10]、kbd:[F11] 或 kbd:[Escape]。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:331
msgid "If the computer loads the existing operating system instead of the FreeBSD installer, then either:"
msgstr "如果计算机加载的是现有的操作系统而不是 FreeBSD 的安装程序，可能因为："

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:333
msgid "The installation media was not inserted early enough in the boot process. Leave the media inserted and try restarting the computer."
msgstr "安装介质在启动过程中没有足够早地插入。让介质继续插入并尝试重新启动计算机。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:334
msgid "The BIOS changes were incorrect or not saved. Double-check that the right boot device is selected as the first boot device."
msgstr "BIOS 更改不正确或没有保存。仔细检查是否选择了正确的启动设备作为第一个启动设备。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:335
msgid ""
"This system is too old to support booting from the chosen media. In this case, the Plop Boot Manager (http://www.plop.at/en/bootmanagers.html[]) "
"can be used to boot the system from the selected media."
msgstr ""
"这个系统太老了，不支持从所选介质启动。在这种情况下，可以使用 Plop Boot Manager (http://www.plop.at/en/bootmanagers.html[]) 从选定的媒体启动系统。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:336
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting on PowerPC(R)"
msgstr "在 PowerPC(R) 上启动"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:341
msgid ""
"On most machines, holding kbd:[C] on the keyboard during boot will boot from the CD.  Otherwise, hold kbd:[Command+Option+O+F], or kbd:[Windows"
"+Alt+O+F] on non-Apple(R) keyboards.  At the `0 >` prompt, enter"
msgstr ""
"在大多数机器上，在启动过程中按住键盘上的kbd:[C] 将从 CD 启动。否则，按住 kbd:[Command+Option+O+F]，或者在非苹果(R)键盘上按住 kbd:[Windows+Alt+O"
"+F]。在 `0>` 提示下，输入"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:345
#, no-wrap
msgid " boot cd:,\\ppc\\loader cd:0\n"
msgstr " boot cd:,\\ppc\\loader cd:0\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:348
#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD Boot Menu"
msgstr "FreeBSD 引导加载器菜单"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:351
msgid "Once the system boots from the installation media, a menu similar to the following will be displayed:"
msgstr "系统从安装介质启动以后，将显示一个类似于下图的菜单："

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:353
#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD Boot Loader Menu"
msgstr "FreeBSD 安装程序"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:354
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-newboot-loader-menu.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-newboot-loader-menu.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:360
msgid ""
"By default, the menu will wait ten seconds for user input before booting into the FreeBSD installer or, if FreeBSD is already installed, before "
"booting into FreeBSD.  To pause the boot timer in order to review the selections, press kbd:[Space].  To select an option, press its highlighted "
"number, character, or key.  The following options are available."
msgstr ""
"默认情况下，在启动到 FreeBSD 安装程序之前，该菜单会等待 10 秒钟让用户输入；如果已经安装了 FreeBSD，则在启动到 FreeBSD 之前。要暂停启动计时器以查看"
"选择，请按空格 kbd:[Space]。要选择一个选项，按其高亮的数字、字符或键。以下是可用的选项。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:362
msgid ""
"`Boot Multi User`: This will continue the FreeBSD boot process. If the boot timer has been paused, press kbd:[1], upper- or lower-case kbd:[B], "
"or kbd:[Enter]."
msgstr "`Boot Multi User`: 这将继续 FreeBSD 的启动过程。如果启动计时器已经暂停，按 kbd:[1]，大写或小写的 kbd:[B]，或 kbd:[Enter] 键。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:363
msgid ""
"`Boot Single User`: This mode can be used to fix an existing FreeBSD installation as described in crossref:boot[boot-singleuser,“Single-User "
"Mode”]. Press kbd:[2] or the upper- or lower-case kbd:[S] to enter this mode."
msgstr ""
"`Boot Single User`: 这个模式可以用来修复现有的 FreeBSD 安装，如crossref:boot[boot-singleuser,“Single-User Mode”] 中所述。按kbd:[2] 或大写或小写的 "
"kbd:[S] 来进入这个模式。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:364
msgid ""
"`Escape to loader prompt`: This will boot the system into a repair prompt that contains a limited number of low-level commands. This prompt is "
"described in crossref:boot[boot-loader,“Stage Three”]. Press kbd:[3] or kbd:[Esc] to boot into this prompt."
msgstr ""
"`Escape to loader prompt`: 这将引导系统进入一个包含有限数量的低级命令的修复提示。这个提示将在 crossref:boot[boot-loader,“Stage Three”] 中描述。按 "
"kbd:[3] 或 kbd:[Esc] 键启动进入这个提示。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:365
msgid "`Reboot`: Reboots the system."
msgstr "`Reboot`: 重启系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:366
msgid "`Kernel`: Loads a different kernel."
msgstr "`Kernel`: 加载一个不同的内核。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:367
msgid "`Configure Boot Options`: Opens the menu shown in, and described under, <<bsdinstall-boot-options-menu>>."
msgstr "`Configure Boot Options`: 打开 <<bsdinstall-boot-options-menu>> 中描述的菜单。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:369
#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD Boot Options Menu"
msgstr "FreeBSD 开机选项菜单"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:370
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-boot-options-menu.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-boot-options-menu.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:374
msgid ""
"The boot options menu is divided into two sections.  The first section can be used to either return to the main boot menu or to reset any toggled "
"options back to their defaults."
msgstr "开机选项菜单分为两个部分。第一部分可以用来返回到主启动菜单或将任何已切换的选项重新设置为默认值。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:378
msgid ""
"The next section is used to toggle the available options to `On` or `Off` by pressing the option's highlighted number or character.  The system "
"will always boot using the settings for these options until they are modified.  Several options can be toggled using this menu:"
msgstr ""
"下一个部分是用来切换可用的选项，通过按下选项的高亮数字或字符来开启或关闭。系统将始终使用这些选项的设置启动，直到它们被修改。有几个选项可以通过这个"
"菜单进行切换："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:380
msgid "`ACPI Support`: If the system hangs during boot, try toggling this option to `Off`."
msgstr "`ACPI Support`: 如果系统在启动过程中挂起，请尝试将该选项切换为 `Off`。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:381
msgid "`Safe Mode`: If the system still hangs during boot even with `ACPI Support` set to `Off`, try setting this option to `On`."
msgstr "`Safe Mode`: 如果即使将 `ACPI Support` 设置为 `Off`，系统在启动时仍然挂起，请尝试将这个选项设置为 `On`。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:382
msgid ""
"`Single User`: Toggle this option to `On` to fix an existing FreeBSD installation as described in crossref:boot[boot-singleuser,“Single-User "
"Mode”]. Once the problem is fixed, set it back to `Off`."
msgstr ""
"`Single User`: 将这个选项切换到 `On` 来修复现有的 FreeBSD 安装，如 crossref:boot[boot-singleuser,“Single-User Mode”] 中所述。如果问题得到解决了，"
"再将其设置为 `Off` 即可。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:383
msgid ""
"`Verbose`: Toggle this option to `On` to see more detailed messages during the boot process. This can be useful when troubleshooting a piece of "
"hardware."
msgstr "`Verbose`: 把这个选项切换到 `On`，可以在启动过程中看到更详细的信息。这在排除一个硬件的故障时可能很有用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:387
msgid ""
"After making the needed selections, press kbd:[1] or kbd:[Backspace] to return to the main boot menu, then press kbd:[Enter] to continue booting "
"into FreeBSD.  A series of boot messages will appear as FreeBSD carries out its hardware device probes and loads the installation program.  Once "
"the boot is complete, the welcome menu shown in <<bsdinstall-choose-mode>> will be displayed."
msgstr ""
"在做出必要的选择后，按 kbd:[1] 或 kbd:[Backspace] 键返回主启动菜单，然后按 kbd:[Enter] 键继续启动 FreeBSD。当 FreeBSD 进行硬件设备探测并加载安装程"
"序时，会出现一系列的启动信息。启动完成了以后，将显示 <<bsdinstall-choose-mode>> 中的欢迎菜单。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:389
#, no-wrap
msgid "Welcome Menu"
msgstr "欢迎菜单"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:390
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-choose-mode.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-choose-mode.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:398
msgid ""
"Press kbd:[Enter] to select the default of btn:[Install] to enter the installer.  The rest of this chapter describes how to use this installer.  "
"Otherwise, use the right or left arrows or the colorized letter to select the desired menu item.  The btn:[Shell] can be used to access a FreeBSD "
"shell in order to use command line utilities to prepare the disks before installation.  The btn:[Live CD] option can be used to try out FreeBSD "
"before installing it.  The live version is described in <<using-live-cd>>."
msgstr ""
"按回车键 kbd:[Enter] ，选择默认的 btn:[Install]，进入安装程序。本章的其余部分将介绍如何使用这个安装程序。否则，使用左右箭头或彩色字母来选择所需的"
"菜单项。btn:[Shell] 可以用来访问一个 FreeBSD shell，以便在安装前使用命令行工具来准备磁盘。btn:[Live CD] 选项可以用来在安装前试用 FreeBSD。Live版本"
"在 <<using-live-cd>> 中有描述。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:404
msgid ""
"To review the boot messages, including the hardware device probe, press the upper- or lower-case kbd:[S] and then kbd:[Enter] to access a shell.  "
"At the shell prompt, type `more /var/run/dmesg.boot` and use the space bar to scroll through the messages.  When finished, type `exit` to return "
"to the welcome menu."
msgstr ""
"要查看开机信息，包括硬件设备探测，按大写或小写的 kbd:[S]，然后按回车键 kbd:[Enter] 进入一个 shell。在 shell 提示符下，输入 `more /var/run/dmesg."
"boot`，并使用空格键滚动浏览信息。完成后，键入 `exit` 来返回欢迎菜单。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:407
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using bsdinstall"
msgstr "使用 bsdinstall"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:412
msgid ""
"This section shows the order of the bsdinstall menus and the type of information that will be asked before the system is installed.  Use the "
"arrow keys to highlight a menu option, then kbd:[Space] to select or deselect that menu item.  When finished, press kbd:[Enter] to save the "
"selection and move onto the next screen."
msgstr ""
"本节显示了bsdinstall菜单的顺序以及在安装系统前将被询问的信息类型。使用方向键选中一个菜单选项，然后用空格 kbd:[Space] 选择或取消选择该菜单项。完成"
"后，按回车键kbd:[Enter] 保存选择并进入下一屏幕。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:414
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting the Keymap Menu"
msgstr "选择键盘类型"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:417
msgid "Before starting the process, bsdinstall will load the keymap files as show in <<bsdinstall-keymap-loading>>."
msgstr "在启动这个过程之前，bsdinstall将加载键盘类型文件，如 <<bsdinstall-keymap-loading>> 所示。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:419
#, no-wrap
msgid "Keymap Loading"
msgstr "加载键盘类型"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:420
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-keymap-loading.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-keymap-loading.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:425
msgid ""
"After the keymaps have been loaded bsdinstall displays the menu shown in <<bsdinstall-keymap-10>>.  Use the up and down arrows to select the "
"keymap that most closely represents the mapping of the keyboard attached to the system.  Press kbd:[Enter] to save the selection."
msgstr ""
"键盘类型文件加载完毕后，bsdinstall会显示 <<bsdinstall-keymap-10>> 中所示的菜单。使用向上和向下的箭头选择最能代表连接到系统的键盘映射的键图。按回车"
"键 kbd:[Enter] 来保存选择。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:427
#, no-wrap
msgid "Keymap Selection Menu"
msgstr "Keymap Selection Menu"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:428
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-keymap-10.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-keymap-10.png"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:434
msgid ""
"Pressing kbd:[Esc] will exit this menu and use the default keymap.  If the choice of keymap is not clear, [.guimenuitem]#United States of America "
"ISO-8859-1# is also a safe option."
msgstr ""
"按 kbd:[Esc] 键将退出这个菜单，并使用默认的键盘图。如果不确定该选择哪一项，美国的 [.guimenuitem]#United States of America ISO-8859-1# 是一个安全的"
"选择。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:437
msgid ""
"In addition, when selecting a different keymap, the user can try the keymap and ensure it is correct before proceeding as shown in <<bsdinstall-"
"keymap-testing>>."
msgstr "此外，当选择不同的键图时，用户可以尝试键图并确保它是正确的，然后再继续进行，如<<bsdinstall-keymap-testing>>所示。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:439
#, no-wrap
msgid "Keymap Testing Menu"
msgstr "Keymap Testing Menu"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:440
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-keymap-testing.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-keymap-testing.png"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:443 content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:448
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting the Hostname"
msgstr "设置主机名"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:446
msgid "The next bsdinstall menu is used to set the hostname for the newly installed system."
msgstr "下一个 bsdinstall 菜单是用来设置新安装系统的主机名。"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:449
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-config-hostname.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-config-hostname.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:453
msgid "Type in a hostname that is unique for the network.  It should be a fully-qualified hostname, such as `machine3.example.com`."
msgstr "键入一个对网络来说是唯一的主机名。它应该是一个完全资格域名，如 `machine3.example.com`。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:455 content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:460
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting Components to Install"
msgstr "选择要安装的组件"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:458
msgid "Next, bsdinstall will prompt to select optional components to install."
msgstr "下面，bsdinstall 将提示选择要安装的组件。"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:461
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-config-components.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-config-components.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:466
msgid ""
"Deciding which components to install will depend largely on the intended use of the system and the amount of disk space available.  The FreeBSD "
"kernel and userland, collectively known as the _base system_, are always installed.  Depending on the architecture, some of these components may "
"not appear:"
msgstr ""
"决定安装哪些组件主要取决于系统的预期用途和可用的磁盘空间大小。FreeBSD 内核和用户空间，统称为_基本系统_，为默认安装。根据架构的不同，其中一些组件可"
"能不会出现："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:468
msgid "`base-dbg` - Base tools like cat, ls among many others with debug symbols activated."
msgstr "`base-dbg` - 基础工具，如cat, ls等，并激活调试符号。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:469
msgid "`kernel-dbg` - Kernel and modules with debug symbols activated."
msgstr "`kernel-dbg` - 激活调试符号的内核和模块。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:470
msgid "`lib32-dbg` - Compatibility libraries for running 32-bit applications on a 64-bit version of FreeBSD with debug symbols activated."
msgstr "`lib32-dbg` - 用于在 64 位的 FreeBSD 上运行 32 位应用程序的兼容库，并激活调试符号。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:471
msgid "`lib32` - Compatibility libraries for running 32-bit applications on a 64-bit version of FreeBSD."
msgstr "`lib32` - 用于在 64 位版本的 FreeBSD 上运行 32 位应用程序的兼容库。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:472
msgid ""
"`ports` - The FreeBSD Ports Collection is a collection of files which automates the downloading, compiling and installation of third-party "
"software packages. crossref:ports[ports,Installing Applications: Packages and Ports] discusses how to use the Ports Collection."
msgstr ""
"`ports` - FreeBSD Ports Collection 是一个文件集，可以自动下载、编译和安装第三方软件包。crossref:ports[ports,安装应用程序：包和 port] 讨论了如何使"
"用 Ports Collection。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:478
msgid ""
"The installation program does not check for adequate disk space.  Select this option only if sufficient hard disk space is available.  The "
"FreeBSD Ports Collection takes up about {ports-size} of disk space."
msgstr "安装程序不检查是否有足够的磁盘空间。请只在有足够的硬盘空间时才选择这个选项。FreeBSD Ports Collection 占用了大约 {ports-size} 的磁盘空间。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:481
msgid ""
"`src` - The complete FreeBSD source code for both the kernel and the userland. Although not required for the majority of applications, it may be "
"required to build device drivers, kernel modules, or some applications from the Ports Collection. It is also used for developing FreeBSD itself. "
"The full source tree requires 1 GB of disk space and recompiling the entire FreeBSD system requires an additional 5 GB of space."
msgstr ""
"`src` - 内核和用户空间的完整 FreeBSD 源代码。尽管大多数应用程序都不需要它，但在制作设备驱动程序、 内核模块，或某些来自 Ports Collection 的应用程序"
"时，可能需要它。它也被用于开发 FreeBSD 本身。完整的源代码树需要 1GB 的磁盘空间，重新编译整个 FreeBSD 系统需要额外的 5GB 空间。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:482
msgid "`tests` - FreeBSD Test Suite."
msgstr "`tests` - FreeBSD 测试套件。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:484 content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:491
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing from the Network"
msgstr "从网络上安装"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:489
msgid ""
"The menu shown in <<bsdinstall-netinstall-notify>> only appears when installing from a [.filename]#-bootonly.iso# or [.filename]#-mini-memstick."
"img# as this installation media does not hold copies of the installation files.  Since the installation files must be retrieved over a network "
"connection, this menu indicates that the network interface must be configured first.  If this menu is shown in any step of the process remember "
"to follow the instructions in <<bsdinstall-config-network-dev>>."
msgstr ""
"从 <<bsdinstall-netinstall-notify>> 中显示的菜单只在从 [.filename]#-bootonly.iso# 或 [.filename]#-mini-memstick.img# 安装时出现，因为这种安装介质"
"没有保存安装文件的副本。由于安装文件必须通过网络连接来获取，这个菜单表明必须先配置网络接口。如果在这个过程的任何步骤中显示这个菜单，请记住按照 "
"<<bsdinstall-config-network-dev>> 的说明进行操作。"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:492
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-netinstall-files.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-netinstall-files.png"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:495
#, no-wrap
msgid "Allocating Disk Space"
msgstr "分配硬盘空间"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:498
msgid "The next menu is used to determine the method for allocating disk space."
msgstr "下一个菜单是用来确定分配磁盘空间的方法。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:500
#, no-wrap
msgid "Partitioning Choices"
msgstr "硬盘分区选项"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:501
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-zfs-partmenu.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-zfs-partmenu.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:504
msgid "bsdinstall gives the user four methods for allocating disk space:"
msgstr "bsdinstall 为用户提供了四种分配磁盘空间的方法："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:506
msgid "`Auto (UFS)` partitioning automatically sets up the disk partitions using the `UFS` file system."
msgstr "`Auto (UFS)` 分区使用 `UFS` 文件系统自动设置磁盘分区。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:507
msgid "`Manual` partitioning allows advanced users to create customized partitions from menu options."
msgstr "`Manual` 分区允许高级用户通过菜单选项创建自定义分区。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:508
msgid ""
"`Shell` opens a shell prompt where advanced users can create customized partitions using command-line utilities like man:gpart[8], man:fdisk[8], "
"and man:bsdlabel[8]."
msgstr "`Shell` 打开一个 shell 提示符，高级用户可以使用 man:gpart[8], man:fdisk[8] 和 man:bsdlabel[8] 等命令行工具创建自定义分区。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:509
msgid "`Auto (ZFS)` partitioning creates a root-on-ZFS system with optional GELI encryption support for _boot environments_."
msgstr "`Auto (ZFS)` 分区创建了一个 root-on-ZFS 系统，并为_启动环境_提供可选的 GELI 加密支持。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:512
msgid ""
"This section describes what to consider when laying out the disk partitions.  It then demonstrates how to use the different partitioning methods."
msgstr "本节描述了在布置磁盘分区时需要考虑的问题。然后，它演示了如何使用不同的分区方法。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:514
#, no-wrap
msgid "Designing the Partition Layout"
msgstr "设计分区布局"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:519
msgid ""
"When laying out file systems, remember that hard drives transfer data faster from the outer tracks to the inner.  Thus, smaller and heavier-"
"accessed file systems should be closer to the outside of the drive, while larger partitions like [.filename]#/usr# should be placed toward the "
"inner parts of the disk.  It is a good idea to create partitions in an order similar to: [.filename]#/#, swap, [.filename]#/var#, and [."
"filename]#/usr#."
msgstr ""
"在布局文件系统时，请记住，硬盘从外部轨道向内部传输数据的速度较快。因此，较小和较大的文件系统应该靠近硬盘的外部，而较大的分区，如 [.filename]#/"
"usr# 应该放在磁盘的内部。以类似的顺序创建分区是个好主意：[.filename]#/#, swap, [.filename]#/var#, [.filename]#/usr#。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:524
msgid ""
"The size of the [.filename]#/var# partition reflects the intended machine's usage.  This partition is used to hold mailboxes, log files, and "
"printer spools.  Mailboxes and log files can grow to unexpected sizes depending on the number of users and how long log files are kept.  On "
"average, most users rarely need more than about a gigabyte of free disk space in [.filename]#/var#."
msgstr ""
"[.filename]#/var# 分区的大小反映了机器的用途。这个分区用来存放邮箱、日志文件和打印机线轴。信箱和日志文件可以增长到意想不到的大小，这取决于用户的数"
"量和日志文件的保存时间。平均来说，大多数用户很少需要超过 [.filename]#/var# 中约一千兆字节的自由磁盘空间。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:530
msgid ""
"Sometimes, a lot of disk space is required in [.filename]#/var/tmp#.  When new software is installed, the packaging tools extract a temporary "
"copy of the packages under [.filename]#/var/tmp#.  Large software packages, like Firefox or LibreOffice may be tricky to install if there is not "
"enough disk space under [.filename]#/var/tmp#."
msgstr ""
"有时，在 [.filename]#/var/tmp# 中需要大量的磁盘空间。当安装新软件时，打包工具会在 [.filename]#/var/tmp# 下提取软件包的临时复制。如果 [.filename]#/"
"var/tmp# 下没有足够的磁盘空间，大型软件包，如 Firefox 或 LibreOffice 的安装可能会很麻烦。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:534
msgid ""
"The [.filename]#/usr# partition holds many of the files which support the system, including the FreeBSD Ports Collection and system source code.  "
"At least 2 gigabytes of space is recommended for this partition."
msgstr "[.filename]#/usr# 分区存放着许多支持系统的文件，包括 FreeBSD Ports Collection 和系统源代码。建议这个分区至少要有 2GB 的空间。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:537
msgid ""
"When selecting partition sizes, keep the space requirements in mind.  Running out of space in one partition while barely using another can be a "
"hassle."
msgstr "在选择分区大小的时候，要牢记空间的要求。一个分区的空间用完了，而另一个分区却几乎用不完，这可能是个麻烦事。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:541
msgid ""
"As a rule of thumb, the swap partition should be about double the size of physical memory (RAM).  Systems with minimal RAM may perform better "
"with more swap.  Configuring too little swap can lead to inefficiencies in the VM page scanning code and might create issues later if more memory "
"is added."
msgstr ""
"作为一个经验法则，交换分区应该是物理内存（RAM）的两倍。拥有最小内存的系统可能会因为有更多的交换空间而表现得更好。配置太小的交换空间会导致虚拟机页"
"面扫描代码的效率低下，如果以后添加更多的内存，可能会产生问题。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:548
msgid ""
"On larger systems with multiple SCSI disks or multiple IDE disks operating on different controllers, it is recommended that swap be configured on "
"each drive, up to four drives.  The swap partitions should be approximately the same size.  The kernel can handle arbitrary sizes but internal "
"data structures scale to 4 times the largest swap partition.  Keeping the swap partitions near the same size will allow the kernel to optimally "
"stripe swap space across disks.  Large swap sizes are fine, even if swap is not used much.  It might be easier to recover from a runaway program "
"before being forced to reboot."
msgstr ""
"在具有多个 SCSI 磁盘或在不同控制器上运行的多个 IDE 磁盘的大型系统上，建议在每个驱动器上配置交换空间，最多可配置四个驱动器。交换分区的大小应该大致"
"相同。内核可以处理任意大小的分区，但是内部数据结构可以扩展到最大交换分区的 4 倍。保持交换分区接近相同的大小将允许内核以最佳的方式在不同的磁盘上剥"
"离交换空间。即使交换空间用得不多，稍大的交换空间也有益。在被迫重启之前，可能更容易从失控的程序中恢复。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:552
msgid ""
"By properly partitioning a system, fragmentation introduced in the smaller write heavy partitions will not bleed over into the mostly read "
"partitions.  Keeping the write loaded partitions closer to the disk's edge will increase I/O performance in the partitions where it occurs the "
"most.  While I/O performance in the larger partitions may be needed, shifting them more toward the edge of the disk will not lead to a "
"significant performance improvement over moving [.filename]#/var# to the edge."
msgstr ""
"通过对系统进行适当的分区，在较小的写入量大的分区中引入的碎片将不会渗入主要读取的分区。让写入量大的分区更接近磁盘的边缘，将提高发生率最高的分区的 "
"I/O 性能。虽然可能需要较大分区的 I/O 性能，但将它们移向磁盘边缘不会比将 [.filename]#/var# 移向边缘带来明显的性能改善。"

