#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:939
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling Services"
msgstr "开启服务"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:944
msgid ""
"The next menu is used to configure which system services will be started whenever the system boots.  All of these services are optional.  Only "
"start the services that are needed for the system to function."
msgstr "下一个菜单用于配置在系统启动时哪些系统服务将被启动。所有这些服务都是可选的。只启动系统运行所需的服务。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:946
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting Additional Services to Enable"
msgstr "选择要启用的其他服务"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:947
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-config-services.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-config-services.png"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:950
msgid "Here is a summary of the services which can be enabled in this menu:"
msgstr "下面是在这个菜单中可以启用的服务的摘要："

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:952
msgid ""
"`local_unbound` - Enable the DNS local unbound. It is necessary to keep in mind that this is the unbound of the base system and is only meant for "
"use as a local caching forwarding resolver. If the objective is to set up a resolver for the entire network install package:dns/unbound[]."
msgstr ""
"`local_unbound` - 启用 DNS 本地非绑定。有必要记住，这是基础系统的 unbound，只作为本地缓存转发解析器使用。如果目标是为整个网络建立一个解析器，请安"
"装package:dns/unbound[]。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:953
msgid ""
"`sshd` - The Secure Shell (SSH) daemon is used to remotely access a system over an encrypted connection. Only enable this service if the system "
"should be available for remote logins."
msgstr "`sshd` - 安全 shell（SSH）守护程序用于通过加密连接远程访问系统。只有在系统应该可用于远程登录的情况下才启用这个服务。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:954
msgid "`moused` - Enable this service if the mouse will be used from the command-line system console."
msgstr "`moused` - 如果要从命令行系统控制台使用鼠标，则启用该服务。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:955
msgid ""
"`ntpdate` - Enable the automatic clock synchronization at boot time. The functionality of this program is now available in the man:ntpd[8] "
"daemon. After a suitable period of mourning, the man:ntpdate[8] utility will be retired."
msgstr ""
"`ntpdate` - 启用启动时的自动时钟同步功能。这个程序的功能现在在 man:ntpd[8] 守护进程中可用。在一段适当的哀悼期之后，man:ntpdate[8] 工具将退役。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:956
msgid ""
"`ntpd` - The Network Time Protocol (NTP) daemon for automatic clock synchronization. Enable this service if there is a Windows(R), Kerberos, or "
"LDAP server on the network."
msgstr "`ntpd` - 用于自动时钟同步的网络时间协议（NTP）守护进程。如果网络上有一个 Windows(R)、Kerberos 或 LDAP 服务器，请启用这个服务。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:957
msgid "`powerd` - System power control utility for power control and energy saving."
msgstr "`powerd` - 用于电源控制和节约能源的系统电源控制工具。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:958
msgid "`dumpdev` - Enabling crash dumps is useful in debugging issues with the system, so users are encouraged to enable crash dumps."
msgstr "`powerd` - 用于电源控制和节约能源的系统电源控制工具。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:960
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling Hardening Security Options"
msgstr "启用强化安全选项"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:965
msgid "The next menu is used to configure which security options will be enabled.  All of these options are optional.  But their use is encouraged."
msgstr "下一个菜单是用来配置哪些安全选项将被启用。所有这些选项都是可选的。但我们鼓励开启它们。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:967
#, no-wrap
msgid "Selecting Hardening Security Options"
msgstr "选择加固安全选项"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:968
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-hardening.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-hardening.png"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:971
msgid "Here is a summary of the options which can be enabled in this menu:"
msgstr "下面是这个菜单中可以启用的选项的摘要："

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:973
msgid ""
"`hide_uids` - Hide processes running as other users to prevent the unprivileged users to see other running processes in execution by other users "
"(UID) preventing information leakage."
msgstr "`hide_uids` - 隐藏以其他用户身份运行的进程，防止非特权用户看到其他用户正在执行的进程（UID），防止信息泄露。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:974
msgid ""
"`hide_gids` - Hide processes running as other groups to prevent the unprivileged users to see other running processes in execution by other "
"groups (GID) preventing information leakage."
msgstr "`hide_gids` - 隐藏以其他组的名义运行的进程，以防止非特权用户看到其他组正在执行的进程（GID），防止信息泄露。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:975
msgid "`hide_jail` - Hide processes running in jails to prevent the unprivileged users to see processes running inside the jails."
msgstr "`hide_jail` - 隐藏在 Jail 中运行的进程，防止非特权用户看到 Jail 中运行的进程。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:976
msgid ""
"`read_msgbuf` - Disabling reading kernel message buffer for unprivileged users prevent from using man:dmesg[8] to view messages from the kernel's "
"log buffer."
msgstr "`read_msgbuf` - 禁止非特权用户使用 man:dmesg[8] 查看内核日志缓冲区的信息，以防止读取内核信息缓冲区。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:977
msgid ""
"`proc_debug` - Disabling process debugging facilities for unprivileged users disables a variety of unprivileged inter-process debugging services, "
"including some procfs functionality, ptrace(), and ktrace(). Please note that this will also prevent debugging tools, for instance man:lldb[1], "
"man:truss[1], man:procstat[1], as well as some built-in debugging facilities in certain scripting language like PHP, etc., from working for "
"unprivileged users."
msgstr ""
"`proc_debug` - 禁用非特权用户的进程调试设施，禁用各种非特权的进程间调试服务，包括一些 procfs 功能、trace() 和 ktrace()。请注意，这也会阻止调试工"
"具，例如 man:lldb[1], man:truss[1], man:procstat[1]，以及某些脚本语言（如 PHP）中的内置调试设施对非特权用户的作用。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:978
msgid "`random_pid` - Randomize the PID of newly created processes."
msgstr "`random_pid` - 随机化新创建进程的 PID。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:979
msgid "`clear_tmp` - Clean [.filename]#/tmp# when the system starts up."
msgstr "`clear_tmp` - 在系统启动时清理 [.filename]#/tmp# 。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:980
msgid ""
"`disable_syslogd` - Disable opening syslogd network socket. By default FreeBSD runs syslogd in a secure way with `-s`. That prevents the daemon "
"from listening for incoming UDP requests at port 514. With this option enabled syslogd will run with the flag `-ss` which prevents syslogd from "
"opening any port. To get more information consult man:syslogd[8]."
msgstr ""
"`disable_syslogd` - 禁止打开 syslogd 网络套接字。在默认情况下，FreeBSD 以安全的方式运行 syslogd，并使用 `-s`。这可以防止守护进程在 514 端口监听传"
"入的 UDP 请求。启用该选项后，syslogd 将以标志 `-ss`运行，它可以防止 syslogd 打开任何端口。要获得更多信息，请参考 man:syslogd[8]。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:981
msgid "`disable_sendmail` - Disable the sendmail mail transport agent."
msgstr "`disable_sendmail` - 禁用 sendmail 邮件传输代理。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:982
msgid "`secure_console` - When this option is enabled, the prompt requests the `root` password when entering single-user mode."
msgstr "`secure_console` - 当这个选项被启用时，在进入单用户模式时，提示要求输入 `root` 密码。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:983
msgid ""
"`disable_ddtrace` - DTrace can run in a mode that will actually affect the running kernel. Destructive actions may not be used unless they have "
"been explicitly enabled. To enable this option when using DTrace use `-w`. To get more information consult man:dtrace[1]."
msgstr ""
"`disable_ddtrace` - DTrace 可以在实际影响运行中的内核的模式下运行。除非明确启用，否则不得使用破坏性的操作。要在使用 DTrace 时启用该选项，请使用 `-"
"w`。要获得更多信息，请查阅 man:dtrace[1]。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:985
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add Users"
msgstr "添加用户"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:991
msgid ""
"The next menu prompts to create at least one user account.  It is recommended to login to the system using a user account rather than as `root`.  "
"When logged in as `root`, there are essentially no limits or protection on what can be done.  Logging in as a normal user is safer and more "
"secure."
msgstr ""
"下一个菜单提示至少要创建一个用户账户。建议使用一个用户账户而不是以 `root` 身份登录系统。当以 `root` 身份登录时，对可以做的事情基本上没有限制或保"
"护。以普通用户身份登录更安全、更有保障。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:993
msgid "Select btn:[Yes] to add new users."
msgstr "选择 btn:[Yes] 来添加新用户。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:995
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add User Accounts"
msgstr "添加用户账户"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:996
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-adduser1.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-adduser1.png"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1000
msgid ""
"Follow the prompts and input the requested information for the user account.  The example shown in <<bsdinstall-add-user2>> creates the `asample` "
"user account."
msgstr "按照提示，输入所要求的用户账户信息。 <<bsdinstall-add-user2>> 中显示的例子创建了一个 `asample` 用户账户。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1002
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enter User Information"
msgstr "输入用户信息"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1003
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-adduser2.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-adduser2.png"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1006
msgid "Here is a summary of the information to input:"
msgstr "以下是需要输入的信息的摘要："

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1008
msgid ""
"`Username` - The name the user will enter to log in. A common convention is to use the first letter of the first name combined with the last "
"name, as long as each username is unique for the system. The username is case sensitive and should not contain any spaces."
msgstr ""
"`Username` - 用户登录时要输入的名字。一个常见的惯例是使用名字的第一个字母与姓氏相结合，只要每个用户名对系统来说是唯一的。用户名是区分大小写的，不"
"应包含任何空格。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1009
msgid "`Full name` - The user's full name. This can contain spaces and is used as a description for the user account."
msgstr "`Full name` - 用户的全名。这可以包含空格，作为用户账户的描述。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1010
msgid "`Uid` - User ID. Typically, this is left blank so the system will assign a value."
msgstr "`Uid` - 用户 ID。通常情况下，这部分留空，所以系统会分配一个值。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1011
msgid "`Login group` - The user's group. Typically this is left blank to accept the default."
msgstr "`Login group` - 用户的组别。典型的情况是留空，以接受默认值。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1012
msgid ""
"`Invite _user_ into other groups?` - Additional groups to which the user will be added as a member. If the user needs administrative access, type "
"`wheel` here."
msgstr "`Invite user into other groups?` - 额外的组，用户将被添加为成员。如果用户需要管理权限，在这里输入 `wheel`。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1013
msgid "`Login class` - Typically left blank for the default."
msgstr "`Login class` - 通常留空以接受默认值。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1014
msgid ""
"`Shell` - Type in one of the listed values to set the interactive shell for the user. Refer to crossref:basics[shells,“Shells”] for more "
"information about shells."
msgstr "`Shell` - 键入一个列出的值来设置用户的交互式 shell。关于 shell 的更多信息，请参考crossref:basics[shells,“Shells”]。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1015
msgid "`Home directory` - The user's home directory. The default is usually correct."
msgstr "`Home directory` - 用户的主目录。默认值通常是正确的。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1016
msgid "`Home directory permissions` - Permissions on the user's home directory. The default is usually correct."
msgstr "`Home directory permissions` - 用户的主目录的权限。默认值通常是正确的。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1017
msgid "`Use password-based authentication?` - Typically `yes` so that the user is prompted to input their password at login."
msgstr "`Use password-based authentication?` - 通常选择 `yes`，这样用户在登录时就会被提示输入他们的密码。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1018
msgid "`Use an empty password?` - Typically `no` as it is insecure to have a blank password."
msgstr "`Use an empty password?` - 通常不使用，因为空白的密码是不安全的。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1019
msgid "`Use a random password?` - Typically `no` so that the user can set their own password in the next prompt."
msgstr "`Use a random password?` - 通常不是，这样用户可以在下一个提示中设置自己的密码。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1020
msgid "`Enter password` - The password for this user. Characters typed will not show on the screen."
msgstr "`Enter password` - 这个用户的密码。输入的字符不会显示在屏幕上。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1021
msgid "`Enter password again` - The password must be typed again for verification."
msgstr "`Enter password` - 这个用户的密码。输入的字符不会显示在屏幕上。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1022
msgid "`Lock out the account after creation?` - Typically `no` so that the user can login."
msgstr "`Lock out the account after creation?` - 通常是 `no`，这样用户就可以登录。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1026
msgid ""
"After entering everything, a summary is shown for review.  If a mistake was made, enter `no` and try again.  If everything is correct, enter "
"`yes` to create the new user."
msgstr "在输入所有内容后，会显示一个摘要供审查。如果犯了一个错误，输入`no`，再试一次。如果一切正确，输入`yes` 来创建新用户。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1028
#, no-wrap
msgid "Exit User and Group Management"
msgstr "退出用户和组的管理"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1029
#, no-wrap
msgid "bsdinstall-adduser3.png"
msgstr "bsdinstall-adduser3.png"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1033
msgid ""
"If there are more users to add, answer the `Add another user?` question with `yes`.  Enter `no` to finish adding users and continue the "
"installation."
msgstr "如果有更多的用户需要添加，请在`Add another user?` 问题上回答 `yes`。输入 `no` 可完成添加用户步骤并继续安装。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1035
msgid "For more information on adding users and user management, see crossref:basics[users-synopsis,“Users and Basic Account Management”]."
msgstr "关于添加用户和用户管理的更多信息，请参阅crossref:basics[users-synopsis,“Users and Basic Account Management”]。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1037 content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1042
#, no-wrap
msgid "Final Configuration"
msgstr "最终配置"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1040
msgid "After everything has been installed and configured, a final chance is provided to modify settings."
msgstr "在所有东西都被安装和配置好之后，提供了一个修改设置的最后机会。"

#. type: Target for macro image
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/bsdinstall/_index.adoc:1043
#, no-wrap
